\title{bci.place portal possible world}
\author{bmorphism}
\import{macros}
\date{2026-03-29}
\taxon{project}

\p{This is a portal possible world: three rooms, rider protocol, and T-55 pipeline as an experience design. It should not be read as the current bench inventory or the canonical stack.}

\p{Enter your name. See your color. Sit in the chair. See the gap between your
name-color and your brain-color.}

\p{A \strong{Rider} is a Hueman — a being defined by hue, not genome. Your color
is computed. Your brain reveals whether you match it.}

\subtree{
\title{The Three Rooms}

\p{The BCI Factory is three rooms and the shimmer between them.}

\table{
  \tr{\th{Room} \th{Domain} \th{Band} \th{Trit} \th{Experience}}
  \tr{\td{\strong{bci.blue}} \td{Inhibition} \td{α suppression} \td{-1} \td{The quiet. Eyes closed. Alpha drops. You become transparent.}}
  \tr{\td{\strong{bci.red}} \td{Activation} \td{β burst} \td{+1} \td{The fire. Motor intent. Beta spikes. You become opaque.}}
  \tr{\td{\strong{bci.place}} \td{Crossover} \td{θ/γ} \td{0} \td{The shimmer between. Where riders are born.}}
}

\p{GF(3) conservation: blue(-1) + place(0) + red(+1) = 0. The three rooms sum
to nothing. What remains is the rider.}
}

\subtree{
\title{How It Works}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Name → Color}: SplitMix64 deterministic hash. Your name seeds the RNG.
    The hue is computed at hardware speed. 1.7M colors/sec.
    ([[bci-0002]])}
\li{\strong{Chair → Wave}: OpenBCI Cyton 8ch EEG at 250Hz. Eight electrodes read your
    cortical surface. The spectral decomposition reveals your brain's actual
    frequency signature.}
\li{\strong{Gap → Rider}: The distance between your name-color and your brain-color
    is the gap. The oscilloscope shows it in real-time. Ratzilla terminal-in-browser
    renders every rider's waveform.}
\li{\strong{Witness → GAY}: Every visit accrues GAY. No signup. No wallet. The token
    doesn't exist until claimed. ([[horse-0006]], [[horse-0007]])}
}
}

