}

\subtree{
\title{Mathematical Foundations (Stacks Project)}

\p{The BCI pipeline's sheaf-theoretic mathematics originates in algebraic geometry. The \strong{Stacks Project} provides the foundations — 114 chapters covering sites, cohomology, descent, and stacks.}

\p{[[xref-0001]] maps each pipeline stage to its Stacks Project antecedents.
[[stk-0000]] is the full chapter index.}

\transclude{xref-0001}
}

\subtree{
\title{Privacy}

\p{Less storage, not more. No reuse of private data except what you explicitly
enter. The goal is simultaneous presence — your waveform exists while you sit,
then it's yours to keep or discard. The oscilloscope is a mirror, not a
database.}
}

\subtree{
\title{T-55 Armor}
\p{Like the T-55's layered armor: sites (outer hull), cohomology (composite),
descent (spall liner), decode (crew compartment). Each layer protects against
signal decoherence. The rider is the crew.}
}
